<div id="para2">
<h1>About the Food</h1>
<h4>Where does the produce come from?</h4>
<p>We currently work with organic food distributors known for high quality produce and emphasizing local sources.  We also have personal relationships with a number of local farms and plan to increase our sourcing directly from farms in the coming months.  Our goal is to provide the healthiest, tastiest ingredients while supporting local, sustainable farming.</p>
<h4>Do I need to wash or peel the produce?</h4>
<p>While we take great care to provide the freshest, high-quality ingredients, it’s always best to wash the produce prior to juicing.  Produce that you would normally peel for consumption (oranges, etc.) should be peeled prior to juicing.  We include instructions on the produce packaging, but feel free to email us at <%= mail_to 'support@farmivore.com' %> if you have any questions.</p>
<h4>Will the recipes vary from week to week?</h4>
<p>We try to enhance the juicing experience by utilizing the freshest, tastiest seasonal produce available.  Some weeks the recipes will be the same, and some weeks we will change it up.  Over time we will work on providing multiple box options to best fit your needs.  We would love to hear from you to tell us what you want!</p>
<h4>Can I substitute recipe options?</h4>
<p>At this time we do not allow for any recipe customization.  That said, we’d love to hear from you about ingredients that you like (or dislike) to help us fine-tune the weekly recipes.  Over time we will have more box options available to give you more choices.
</p>

<span class="right"><%= link_to "Back to top", "#" %></span><br />
